attractive molecular state

00:06:19.580 --> 00:06:22.950
below, and those two
states repel each other.

00:06:22.950 --> 00:06:25.020
So the repulsion
up here is actually

00:06:25.020 --> 00:06:28.300
caused by the molecular
state down there.

00:06:28.300 --> 00:06:30.270
So in other words,
if you go from

00:06:30.270 --> 00:06:32.790
the attractive to
the repulsive side--

00:06:32.790 --> 00:06:37.070
many people use it, in terms
of pairs-- you go actually

00:06:37.070 --> 00:06:39.190
from very weak
attraction, which is not

00:06:39.190 --> 00:06:40.940
sufficient to form
the bound state,

00:06:40.940 --> 00:06:43.090
to stronger and
stronger attraction,

00:06:43.090 --> 00:06:47.871
which now forms a stronger, and
more strongly bound molecule.

