00:19:21.530 --> 00:19:23.510
equation, which you write down.

00:19:23.510 --> 00:19:25.820
You can transform
the radial equation

00:19:25.820 --> 00:19:27.910
with a more
complicated derivative

00:19:27.910 --> 00:19:31.910
into something which is exactly
a 1D Schrodinger equation.

00:19:31.910 --> 00:19:32.410
Yes.

00:19:32.410 --> 00:19:34.366
AUDIENCE: You can
[INAUDIBLE] relationship

00:19:34.366 --> 00:19:35.344
between [INAUDIBLE]

00:19:38.544 --> 00:19:39.210
PROFESSOR: Sure.

00:19:39.210 --> 00:19:41.157
Uncertainty of relation
always can immediately

00:19:41.157 --> 00:19:42.990
help you if you have
an uncertainty relation

00:19:42.990 --> 00:19:45.260
for for kinetic
energy and you realize

00:19:45.260 --> 00:19:48.770
that you don't have enough
potential, but maybe

00:19:48.770 --> 00:19:51.020
mathematically, what
is different between

00:19:51.020 --> 00:19:54.790
the identically-looking
