00:49:34.380 --> 00:49:36.900
But now we have to be a
little bit more subtle.

00:49:36.900 --> 00:49:41.690
So what we should now define,
is a pairing mean field.

00:49:41.690 --> 00:49:46.350
Not an expectation value of
c 0, but an expectation value

00:49:46.350 --> 00:49:49.800
of this creational annihilation
operators four pairs.

00:49:49.800 --> 00:49:54.410
A little bit more abstract,
but it follows the same logic.

00:49:54.410 --> 00:49:57.640
And then we do the
decoupling approximation,

00:49:57.640 --> 00:50:00.580
which I lectured about to you
