00:51:17.720 --> 00:51:22.990
that those transforming
Fermionic operators,

00:51:22.990 --> 00:51:27.360
we want to make sure that
after transformation we

00:51:27.360 --> 00:51:30.700
fulfill Fermionic commutator.

00:51:30.700 --> 00:51:32.300
And then we determine
coefficients

00:51:32.300 --> 00:51:43.630
in such a way that
cross-terms cancel out,

00:51:43.630 --> 00:51:47.030
and what we obtain now is
a diagonalized Hamiltonian.

00:51:47.030 --> 00:51:50.590
It's diagonalized, it has
the ground state energy.

00:51:50.590 --> 00:51:52.750
And this, you now
realize, this is

00:51:52.750 --> 00:51:54.690
nothing like an
harmonic oscillator.

00:51:54.690 --> 00:51:58.460
It's a quasi particle gas
of independent excitations.

00:51:58.460 --> 00:52:02.260
Gamma k is an excitation
with energy E K,

00:52:02.260 --> 00:52:05.430
and this means we've
diagonalized the problem.

